  "critical": false,
  "description": "Advanced vacuum systems for semiconductor manufacturing: roughing pumps (rotary vane, scroll, diaphragm), high-vacuum pumps (turbomolecular, diffusion), UHV pumps (cryopumps, ion pumps, NEG), vacuum chamber design (stainless steel 304L/316L, CF/ISO-KF sealing), and vacuum measurement (ionization gauges, RGA, helium leak detection). Distinct discipline from gas handling — vacuum engineering focuses on gas removal and controlled-atmosphere environments at pressures from 760 Torr to 10⁻¹¹ Torr.",
